[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{With 10 HCP and 10 red cards you have a good enough hand for an immediate DONT bid. So you bid 2\D, promising that suit and a Major.

Partner responds 2\H.  

Don't get carried away, partner isn't really bidding a \H suit as much as he is letting you know he doesn't like \Ds. You were only competing for a partscore and here you are in a partscore. You pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "N:K7.Q75.KQT4.AQT2 A92.AKJT63.73.65 QJT83.4.J92.KJ84 654.982.A865.973"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1NT X pass 2C pass 2H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "155e917449dfa2d79b5976a13609dc23e6707e848577d53d78f5274d262a49f4"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a terrible hand but you still cannot pass partner's double. He is requesting you to bid 2\C as a relay bid so he can name his suit.

You dutifully respond 2\C and he says 2\H.  

You didn't want to bid the first time, this time you definitely pass.}

